  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Roll out puff pastry to a thickness of 1/8 inch (3 mm).",
    "Cut into 12 equal squares.",
    "In a small bowl, whisk together garlicky yogurt, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Place a tablespoon of marinated tempeh in the center of each square.",
    "Brush edges with garlicky yogurt mixture and fold pastry in half to form triangles.",
    "Place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and brush tops with remaining garlicky yogurt mixture.",
    "Bake for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.",
    "Garnish with chopped parsley and dill, if desired.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!"
